{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with this child (S3 Thread ref + source mode through the code-reading gates)]\n\nAudited this child's contribution to the parent's acceptance/success criteria; every absence cross-checked against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 6d56, S2 70c7, S4 30b3, S5 b7fa, S6 1ba5). This child is the gate-threading / re-rooting slice; the union of children covers every parent criterion. No uncovered parent criterion. Empty G3 findings list.\n\n4-bucket coverage map (parent AC -> covering child/children; this child's role called out):\n- Parent AC1 (no attested gate reads the working tree; all read a faithful snapshot materialized at the pinned SHA) — FULLY covered, with THIS child as the PRIMARY OWNER of the re-rooting half: its AC1 (each of the five gates accepts ref+source; attested reads the snapshot dir, NEVER the server working tree), its AC4 (server's own checked-out branch no longer affects attested verdicts; the wrong-branch false-negative regression test passes), its AC5 (repo_root only locates the object DB; verified code is the snapshot). The faithful-materialization half (byte-match committed tree, export-ignore, LFS/submodule) is S1 (6d56 AC1/AC2). Heart of this child. Clean.\n- Parent AC2 (signed verdict records verified_at_sha + reproducible over identical content) — FULLY covered by S4 (30b3 record+sign+in-toto) with the immutable-SHA basis from S1. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child: it threads the ref and points the gate at the pinned-SHA snapshot but does not sign (its Scope: \"Out: the signing rules (S4)\"). Not an absence (S4 covers signing; this child's AC4 supplies the snapshot-only basis that makes reproducibility achievable).\n- Parent AC3 (local mode reads in-place checkout AND cannot produce a signed verdict) — FULLY covered, SPLIT cleanly: THIS child is the PRIMARY OWNER of the \"reads in-place checkout\" half (its AC2: local reads the in-place checkout, dirty allowed, and is flagged unsigned); S4 owns the \"cannot sign\" enforcement half (its AC2: a local/dirty run never emits a signature). Clean producer/enforcer split (this child marks-unsigned, S4 bars-signing); no double-implementation, no uncovered half.\n- Parent AC4 (concurrent gates on same/different SHAs run without git-lock contention or cross-op corruption; no worktrees; atomic population; delete-on-last-close) — FULLY covered by S1 (atomic population, no-worktree, no index.lock/config.lock contention) + S2 (single-flight, delete-on-last-close). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child (its Scope: \"Out: the snapshot/cache internals (S1/S2)\"); claims none. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC5 (snapshot cache + janitor reclaim disk under pressure without disrupting in-flight reads) — FULLY covered by S2 (sole owner). Explicitly out of this child's scope (S1/S2). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC6 (private-repo fetch failure surfaces a descriptive, actionable credential error) — FULLY covered by S1 (raises; its AC5) + S6 (documents; its AC2). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child; the coalesced fetch is S1's step. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC7 (portable: no external tar; no hardcoded /tmp; flock+mkdir fallback) — FULLY covered by S1 (implementation; its AC4) + S6 (docs; its AC5). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC8 (all six child stories closed; make lint + full test suite green) — STRUCTURAL/meta epic-completion criterion; covered by the existence of all six children (this child is story #3 of 6 in the roster) + each child's own green-bar obligation. Not an absence at this child.\n\nSuccess-criteria narrative (\"every code-reading gate verifies a client-specified, immutable, reproducible snapshot of the project at a pinned SHA — NEVER the server's mutable checkout — safely under concurrent use ...; signed verdicts reproducible and bound to verified_at_sha; unsigned local preserves verify-before-push\") decomposes onto AC1-AC3. The \"NEVER the server's mutable checkout\" clause is precisely this child's core deliverable: its AC1/AC4/AC5 re-root every gate off cwd/repo_root onto the snapshot and prove it via the wrong-branch regression test that motivates the epic. The \"client-specified\" surfacing is S5; \"signed/reproducible/verified_at_sha\" is S4 atop the SHA basis this child threads; \"unsigned local preserves verify-before-push\" is reinforced by this child's AC2 (in-place dirty read, flagged unsigned). No uncovered obligation introduced.\n\nNote: this child's \"What\"/Scope explicitly delegates to named consumers — signing rules to S4, CLI/MCP surface schemas to S5, snapshot/cache internals to S1/S2. Each delegated obligation is claimed by the named sibling (S4 30b3; S5 b7fa; S1 6d56; S2 70c7) — covered-by-named-consumer, not absences.\n\nCoverage-pairing note (clean for G3): this child (S3) and S5 (b7fa) both name ref+source on the SAME five tool surfaces (review_plan/verify_completion/review_ticket/review_code/scan_spec). S3 threads the parameters into the gate dispatch and re-roots the file tools; S5 exposes them on the CLI/MCP schema with defaults. Producer/surface split, each scoped out of the other (S3: \"Out: ... CLI/MCP surface schemas (S5)\"; S5: \"Out: the underlying behavior (S1-S4)\"). No double-ownership, no coverage gap.\n\nNote (scope, not a G3 finding): the existing G4 review on sibling S4 (30b3) flags a seam/dependency-gap around routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py's dependency_hashes() / claim-gate freshness re-check — a seam between S3 and S4 that neither lists attest.py in file_impact. That is a consistency (G4) concern about WHO threads the snapshot handle into the plan-review hashing path, NOT a G3 union-coverage gap: the corresponding parent obligation (AC1 snapshot-only reads, AC2 reproducibility, and the ref-coherence clause) is still CLAIMED by a child (this child re-roots the gate code root; S4 claims claim-gate ref-coherence in its AC4). G3 union-coverage of the parent criteria is therefore complete; the WHO-threads-it question is left to the G4 channel.\n\nConclusion: this child cleanly covers the gate-threading slice (ref+source on all five gates, attested snapshot re-rooting, local in-place unsigned read, repo_root-as-object-DB-only, wrong-branch regression) of the parent criteria — it is the primary owner of the re-rooting half of parent AC1 and the in-place-read half of AC3; no parent acceptance/success criterion is left uncovered by the roster. No G3 finding for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782520484121981001,"uuid":"180b1925-e2fd-4ac9-a2c3-03c0eb4247bc"}